OL,6,F"That is why we have been working so
OL,7,Fhard, including with the Treasury and
OL,8,Fthe UK government, to make
OL,9,Frepresentations on this. And that's
OL,10,Fwhy we do believe that today's
OL,11,Fdecision will keep costs to families
OL,12,Fat an absolute minimum. It means that
OL,13,Fon a domestic property with an average
OL,14,Fcapital value of #123,000 they would
OL,15,Fpay just under #2 more a month. We
OL,16,Funderstand absolutely that families
OL,17,Fare under pressure, families are
OL,18,Fconcerned, there's also local
OL,19,Fgovernment rates increases and this
OL,20,Fwill mean that there is a very small
OL,21,Fand minimal increase in terms of what
OL,22,Fthey have to pay.
